This paper discusses reinforcement learning agents and their hierarchy, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the ability to deal with long time horizons, which is a characteristic of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the transferability of sub-policies to tasks outside the training distribution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
